{"/service/ndnp/tu/batch_tu_kathy_ver01/data/sn89058321/00415621486/1920121001/1123.xml":{"full_text":"iMy Shitig&m More Days\n4\ndl\nI\nBetter hurry and get your selection. We will put away any gift you select\nand deliver when you say. We have a complete delivery service.\nYou have a corner in your living room\nfor a Macey, that a Macey will fit\nOf course, we always have the best line\nof Rockers and chairs that can be\nfound, at pre-war prices\nTone is the Test\na-\"\nU14\nml\nof a Phonograph\nThe scientifically correct acoustic design of\nthe Columbia Grafonola permits the full, free\ndevelopment of the sound waves, and gives you\ngood music, unmufHed unmarred.\nThe Columbia Non,-Set Automatic Stop,\nan absolutely exclusive feature of Columbia -Grafonolas,\ngives the last touch of realism by\nstopping the record when the end is reached.\nThe cabinet with fifteen exclusive\nfeatures for the .wife\n'X\ntheWorld to Meet Your Wishes\nWhy not protect your valued books\nwith a Macey? It is best.\nCome in and let us demonstrate the Columbia to you. We also have Victrolas.\nHaipole Walker Furniture Company\nWhitesell Harpole, Phone 354 j& Undertakers and Embalmers, Phone 99 J. L. Ranson, Jr., Phone 432\nThe Commercial, Union City, Tenn.\nFRIDAY, DECEMBER 10, 1920.\nTHREE NOTED THUGS\nMURDER MEMPHIS JAILER\nI will see you\nCreorge Reeves Diet After He Wounds\nSlayer.\nGeorge Reeves, county Jailer, is\ndead and three gunmen and safe\nblowers known 00 the \"dandy ban\ndit\" trio are at large pursued by\nyery available officer in the city fol\nlowing a sensational but hurriedly\nplanned jail delivery at the county\nJail Tuesday shortly after 11 o'clock.\nThe men at large are:\nAlden Shaw, Clyde Hamilton and\nE. B. Kolly. Hamilton fired the shot\nwhich resulted in Reeves' death.\nHamilton was wounded three times\nbut made his escape bleeding pro\nfusely. Reeves died at St. Joseph's Hos\npital one hour after he was hit.\nThe 3ingle shot which proved fatal\nto the Jailer, according to hospital\nauthorities, entered the lower left\nabdomen, severing a main artery.\nReeves was conscious to within three\nminutes of his death, hospital at\ntaches declare. Ho was attended by\nDr. Battle Malone.\nJAILER SHOOTS BANDIT.\nReeves shot Hamilton after taking\nthe bandit's own gun from him:\nHamilton was lying in the Jail door\nway when his pal, Shaw, handed the\nprostrate bandit a- second pistol.\nHp mil ton raised himoslf on his el\nbow and pulled the trigger once with\nfatal results.\nThe escape came within a few min\nutes after a conference between the\nthreo robbero and an attorney. It\n-was said by sveral jc.il attaches that\na fifth man was in the conference,\nut this could not bo verified. Some\nofficers believed that the bandit se\ncured their guns Tuesday.\nAbe Waldauer, attorney for Ham\nilton, was summoned to the ettorney\njreneral's of flco by Sam O. Bates,\nState prosecutor, at coon. Bates said\n\"Waldauer was In conference with his\n-client Tuesday.\nkelly,' Shaw and Hamilton with an\nattorney were locked in the confer\nence room come minutes before 11\no'clock. The dead Jailer had placed\nthem there. WhenQthe conference\nendod the attorney waved his hand\nto the bandits saying:.\n\"Goodbye, Doys,\nlater.\"\nReeves then turned to the trio and\nsaid:\n\"Come along.\"\nHe Intended returning them to\ntheir cell. The conference room and\nthe bandits' cells are on the first\nfloor. Hamilton poked a pistol In\nReeves' stomach as the jailer turned\naround, saying:\n\"Put 'em up quick.\"\nRQeveo did not comply, but grap\npled with thobandit.\nKatherine Amnion, woman prison\ner, was on the landing above and\nrushod to the aid of the jailer. Han\nilton and Reeves, still struggling,\nbrushed her aside when she first\nreached them. This ontbled Reeves\nto secure the ristol. Hamilton then\nthrew the woman against the iron\nstair railing and ran for the door.\nThe cold blooded murder was par\ntially avenged at 'Winona, Miss.,\nWednesday morning about 10 o'clock\nwhen Clyde Hamilton, the slayer,\ndied witli a pistol bullet through his\nhead.\nThe shot that killed the bandit\nva3 fired by Marshal J. A. Glenn, of\nWinona, after Sheriff R. M. Smith of\nMontgomery County had dropped the\nman by a shot from his revolver\nHamilton .died as many H)ad men\ndie, with gun iu hand and firing at\nthe men who represented the majesty\nof toe law!\nThe murderers have been indicted\nfor murder in first degree and trial\nset for next Monday.\nKelly and Shaw submitted with\nout resistance. Neither of them was\naimed. Memphis News-Scimitar.\nA Happy Accident.\nMiss Gushmore I hear you're the\nman who invented that cuto little\nCharlie Chaplin subnasal mustache.\nHow did you ever happen to think\nof it?\nMr. Zitt It happened is way. I\nhad trouble getting my safety razor\nunder my nose, so I just shaved the\nrest of my face and let itsprout\nthere.\nHens Kept in Clean House Lay Most\nEggs.-\nThe condition of their winter\nquarters is a potent factor upon the\nproductivity pf poultry flocks. Only\nhealthy, contented hens produce eggs\nin paying numbers.\nWhile on range hens both lay and\npay, because conditions are such that\nthey are perfectly healthy. Sanita\ntion takes care of itself and constant\nexorcise, coupled with natural selec\ntion' of food having widely differing\nproperties, gives Ideal conditions for\nhigh production. Because conditions\ndiffer widely in those particulars\nduring the seasons when fowls are\nconfined, results are not as satisfac\ntory.\n\"To counteract unsatisfactory re\nsults,\" poultry specialists say, \"prop\ner sanitary measures must be prac\nticed. Clean and disinfect the house\nthoroly. Remove and burn all floor\nand nest litters. Remove all fittings,\nsuch as nest, roost, roo3ting plat\nforms and water stands. Clean and\npaint with a good liquid disinfectant\nKerosene to which has been added a\nlittle strong, crude carbolic acid\nserves the purpose o,s do several com\nmercial disinfectants. Brush down\nthe wails and ceiling, remove as\nmuch of the old earth as seems neces\nsary, paint the walls with the same\ndisinfectant as the fittings and put\nin fine or Bandy loam to the depth\nof four to six inchoa.\"\nWhen He Needs a Friend.\nThe Stenog.\n\"Who hired that stenographer?\"\n\"My husband won't admit it,\nsaid Mrs. Senior Partner.-\nNor mine,\" declared Mrs. Junior\nPartner.\n\"I guess the offce boy must have\npicked her out. And we can hardly\nblame him for having musical com\nedy tastes.\" Louisville Courier-Jour\nnal.\nYe Old Time Humor.\nTwo knaves walked past a gallows.\nSaid the one: Now Pedro, where\nwould ye bo if yon gallows had Its\ndue?\nSecond Knave Walking alone,\nAdolphus, walking alone. Houston\nPost.\nThe following article is taken from\ntho first page of the New York\nWorld of November 30:\nBuffalo, Nov. 29. Within the\npast 48 hours, more than 1,000 ne\ngroes, discharged during the recent\nbusiness depression, have been forced\nout of Buffalo by the police. Raids\nhave been conducted in the negro\ndistricts and those who are unem\nployed are arrested.\nMany negroes, becoming fright\nened, have left of their n accord.\nSome of these withdrew liberal\namount? from savings banks and de\nparted for the South. .Pawnbrokers\nreport that many pawiftftl clothing\nand jewelry to enable them to get\naway. Employers are not disturbed,\nS3 there has been a surplus of labor\nin Buffalo for several months.\nThis article is in lino with many\nothers that are appearing daily in\nthe Northern and Eastern news\npapers. It is the old story of the negro be\ning pursuaded to go north lor higher\nwages, bettor conditions and other\ninducements that are offered when\never there is a labor shortage.\nIt 13 the 01a story or the negro\nbeing the first to be discharged and\nrun out of town when there is a\nsurplus of labor in the North.\nTor\nOne handsome Bedroom Suite of Walnut,\nas good as new, consisting of one extra large\nvanity Dresser and Chair, one Dresserobe,\none Chifforette, one Bed and heavy weight\nSprings, all-cotton Matress, one Wilton\nDrugget,' one Reed Rocker, one Child's\nBed, one extra heavy solid oak Dining Ta\nble, 6 Chairs, one Crex Rug, one Perfection\n4-burner-Oil Stove with\" Boss oven, Cook\ning Utensils and dishes. Will sacrifice same.\nPHONE459-W\nnnnnnnnnannnE\nAccept\nNo Substitutes\nfor\nThedford's\nBLACMOi\np\nPurely fi\nVegetable\nI Liver Medicine\nnnaoosonnooon\nThe Two Greatest News Gathering and Dis\ntributing Organizations in the World\nFurnish\nThe News Scimitar\nMemphis, Tenn.\nWith all the News of the World\nas soon as it happens.\nThe News Scimitar Has the Exclusive Week Day\nService of r\nThe Associated Press\nAnd the Complete Wire Report of\nThe International News Service\nThe Greatest World News Service of any JPaper in\nThis Section of the South\nFirst in Kews. First In Interesting Features\nMail Your Subscription Today\nTrial Offer One Month. 60c; Three Months. $1.70;\nSix Months, $3.00; One Year. 16.00\nI\nft\nu\nIt","height":"28288","width":"20684"}}
